                        {
                            "key": "XT-30157",
                            "title": "Cost variance management on purchase invoices",
                            "highlight": false,
                            "content_parts": [
                                {
                                    "content": "<p>The cost variance between the purchase receipt and purchase invoice is recorded in stock as a stock value correction. In the stock journal, the variance is recorded as an absorbed or non-absorbed amount depending on the remaining receipted quantity.</p>",
                                    "taxonomies": "all"
                                }
                            ],
                            "taxonomies": {
                                "software": [
                                    "multi-tenant"
                                ],
                                "version": [
                                    "22.0.0"
                                ]
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "key": "XT-29191",
                            "title": "US tax calculation on purchasing documents",
                            "highlight": false,
                            "content_parts": [
                                {
                                    "content": "<p>For the US, tax is calculated for purchasing documents using the internal tax engine.</p><p>Basic settings for tax categories and tax solution are provided, but additional settings are needed to link tax rates to document lines.</p>",
                                    "taxonomies": "all"
                                }
                            ],
                            "taxonomies": {
                                "software": [
                                    "multi-tenant"
                                ],
                                "version": [
                                    "22.0.0"
                                ]
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "key": "XT-15358",
                            "title": "US tax calculation for sales invoices and credit memos",
                            "highlight": false,
                            "content_parts": [
                                {
                                    "content": "<p>For the US, tax is calculated for sales invoices and credit memos using the Avalara integration.</p>",
                                    "taxonomies": "all"
                                }
                            ],
                            "taxonomies": {
                                "software": [
                                    "multi-tenant"
